Correct
[{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg949\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\lang1042\f0\fs18 Black should hit the vital point at 1. Even though White can capture this stone with 2, Black will raise the sacrifice at 3 and then cut at 5 to squeeze the white stones. This capturing technique is called "stone pagoda' and makes sure to allow White no more than two liberties to win the capturing race.
\par
\par }
